      {
        "id": 3015713,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-10-31T19:13:19.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"165252\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks, William. On the WA website, it lists the wines you reviewed under the name \u201cDaniel et Julien Barraud.\u201d If I see a different label for the equivalent wine (i.e., \u201cPouilly-Fuisse En France\u201d), it should be the same wine as the one you reviewed?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes!</p>\n<p>When I taste there, I\u2019m tasting unlabelled bottles. So it may be that they\u2019ve changed the label and what I\u2019m entering is out-of-date.</p>",
