      {
        "id": 3016559,
        "name": "Robert Panzer",
        "username": "Robert_Panzer",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/e56c9b/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-11-02T01:14:44.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I\u2019ve imported Barraud since the 2010 vintage.<br>\nI think that it has been several years that the wines read Daniel and Julien Barraud.<br>\nIf there are differences on the front labels to different importers, (which would be unusual) it is the same wine.<br>\nThere were a few bottlings, maybe the Chataigners and the St Veran Arpege?, from purchased fruit from other family members that were labelled under Julien Barraud.<br>\nBut En France is an estate wine, and has always been.<br>\nSant\u00e9</p>",
