        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/pat_martin/{size}/1547_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-07-17T16:46:36.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Had the 2017 Domaine Barraud en Buland VV Pouilly-Fuisse last night. Wow, killer juice. Terrific depth, intensity, length in an herbal-kaffir lime motif (not the lemon and vanilla of C\u00f4te d\u2019Or nor the tropical fruits of Santa Cruz mountains). Very impressive and worthy of the price premium over most other Pouilly Fuisse. Thanks to WK for putting this on the radar with a spot-on note.</p>",
